depending on the issue - but it would only be for a couple of seconds.\r\n> \r\n> WDYT @John-44\r\n\r\n@benjthayer yes I agree with everything in your message above.\r\n\r\nThe error banners are currently either:\r\n1. over sensitive, triggered too easily for problems that will resolve themselves a second or two later\r\n2. are displayed as a result of errors that need to be fixed (e.g. the solution to the error banner being displayed is to prevent the error occurring too frequently.\r\n\r\nWhat @benjthayer has suggested is a good solution to 1.  If they don't already exist, there should be issues opened to fix the root cause of error banners being displayed in order to fix 2.\r\n\r\nThe 'Backup seed phrase banner' isn't an error banner, and should always be visible after account creation. \r\n",
